Sentencas: Three-layered ceramic membranes based on stabilized zirconia for planar solid-oxide fuel cell (SOFC) are prepared by the tape casting method.
Titulo: Three-Layered Membranes for Planar Solid Oxide Fuel Cells of the Electrolyte-Supported Design: Characteristics and Applications

Sentencas: The outer layers containing 94 mol % ZrO2-6 mol % Sc2O3 provide the enhanced mechanical stability; the inner layer has the composition of 89 mol % ZrO2-10 mol % Sc2O3-1 mol % Y2O3 which has the highest anionic conductivity in the series of solid solutions ZrO2-Y2O3-Sc2O3.
Titulo: Three-Layered Membranes for Planar Solid Oxide Fuel Cells of the Electrolyte-Supported Design: Characteristics and Applications

Sentencas: Studying the mechanical characteristics shows that the ultimate strength (bending strength) of these membranes much exceeds the value typical of single-layered samples.
Titulo: Three-Layered Membranes for Planar Solid Oxide Fuel Cells of the Electrolyte-Supported Design: Characteristics and Applications

Sentencas: The anionic conductivity of three-layered ceramics is studied by the impedance spectroscopy in the frequency range from 1Hz to 1 MHz.
Titulo: Three-Layered Membranes for Planar Solid Oxide Fuel Cells of the Electrolyte-Supported Design: Characteristics and Applications

Sentencas: Membrane-electrode assemblies for SOFCs are fabricated and their electrochemical properties are studied under the conditions of fuel cell operation.
Titulo: Three-Layered Membranes for Planar Solid Oxide Fuel Cells of the Electrolyte-Supported Design: Characteristics and Applications
